translation.Name: Greece Newspaper #2
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_0: PRESIDENT ESTEVAO DECLARES NATION WIDE STATE OF EMERGENCY
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_4: For the protection of our citizens, I am declaring a nation wide state of emergency effective immediately
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_5: Yesterday, President Estevao issued a nation wide state of emergency before being rushed off by special forces.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_6: Prime Minister Yevgeni stayed behind to provide limited answers on the situation.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_7: This is a first step to secure our nation from the pandemic sweeping the globe; we are taking every possible measure to keep everyone safe.
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_8: Reporter Peter Lyosha asked about when the state of emergency will be repealed, to which Yevgeni stated: "At this point in time we are unable to say."
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_9: He also urged everyone to "Keep calm and carry on life as normal." Any other questions asked where met with no comment.
